node.text:
“I basically spent 2020 indoors, and when I was bored in the middle of quarantine, for the first time ever I started playing with make-up,” says #EizaGonzález. Watch the star of ‘Godzilla Vs Kong’ reveal her go-to make-up tricks for statement eyes. 

Directed by @RJGoni.

node.text: Join #BritishVogue’s beauty and lifestyle director Jessica Diner, as she takes you through this month’s edit of products for Vogue Insiders to start trialling at home. Featuring brilliant transformative @EsteeLauderUK, @Aerin and @BeautyPie hero products, watch as Jessica talks through the beauty team favourites.

node.text:
Racing down LA’s Melrose Avenue in the California sun, supermodel #AlessandraAmbrosio takes on Vogue’s latest Shopping Challenge. The goal? She must style three animal-print outfits for three occasions, in just 60 minutes. Watch as she embraces her wild side as she styles a selection of looks for a brunch, job interview and party. 

This episode of The Shopping Challenge was filmed pre-pandemic and before social distancing guidelines were issued.

node.text: “I definitely feel like young girls are being made to grow up far quicker than they are and not celebrating the actual age they are at,” CEO of @BlackGirlFest, @NKrystal_, tells #BritishVogue in the second instalment of @TheOfficialPandora’s speaker series: ‘10 Minutes With’. Watch as the young entrepreneur talks through her inspirations, mentors and how embracing your own uniqueness can be used to your advantage.

Directed by @Julia_Muecke.

node.text: It’s a well-known fact that wearing SPF is one of the best ways to protect your skin – but how do you do it right to avoid signs of ageing and pigmentation? Watch as #BritishVogue’s beauty and lifestyle director @JessicaDiner does a sunscreen deep dive with @LaRochePosay dermatologist Dr Hiva Fassihi to discuss how to incorporate SPF into your everyday make-up routine (and why make-up with SPF isn’t enough), the difference between the effects of ultraviolet A and ultraviolet B on your skin, and why it’s important to apply sunscreen even if you’re not leaving the house.

node.title: Face Facts: The Importance Of SPF No Matter The Season

node.text: As Couture Week gets underway, go behind the scenes at #ParisFashionWeek with actor and model #SukiWaterhouse. node.text: From her signature beehive to her singular musical talent, Amy Winehouse left an indelible impression on the world. Singer-songwriter @DionneOfficial was a child when she first met Winehouse, and the bond they developed was such that Amy not only became her musical mentor, but her honorary godmother. A decade after the star’s untimely death at the age of 27, Dionne pens a heartfelt letter to an irreplaceable mentor – and her biggest champion – at the link in bio.

“I basically spent 2020 indoors, and when I was bored in the middle of quarantine, for the first time ever I started playing with make-up,” says #EizaGonzález. Watch the star of ‘Godzilla Vs Kong’ reveal her go-to make-up tricks for statement eyes. 

Directed by @RJGoni.

node.text: There are few films as eagerly anticipated as #Dune, and with #TimotheeChalamet and #Zendaya as the lead actors, it’s not hard to see why. Based on the cult sci-fi novel, the film – set in the distant future – follows Paul, played by @TChalamet, as he tries to prevent the destruction of the universe. Click the link in bio to watch the trailer.

node.text: Join #BritishVogue’s beauty and lifestyle director Jessica Diner, as she takes you through this month’s edit of products for Vogue Insiders to start trialling at home. Featuring brilliant transformative @EsteeLauderUK, @Aerin and @BeautyPie hero products, watch as Jessica talks through the beauty team favourites.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by British Vogue on July 22, 2021. May be a black-and-white image of 1 person, standing and suit.

node.text:
Exciting news from the @Marvel Universe: Emmy-nominated actor, director and screenwriter Michaela Coel has joined the cast of ‘Black Panther: Wakanda Forever’, the sequel to the Oscar-winning blockbuster #BlackPanther. Details of Coel’s character are still under wraps, but fans are already gearing up for the highly-anticipated follow-up. Click the link in bio for more details, including when it’ll be released and returning cast members.

#MichaelaCoel photographed by @AmyTroostPhotography, with make-up by @JustinePurdue and nails by Amy Vega for the February 2018 issue of #BritishVogue.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by British Vogue on July 21, 2021 tagging @dukeandduchessofcambridge. May be an image of 1 person, child, standing and sky.

node.text: #PrinceGeorge is turning eight - and is cuter than ever. As per their family tradition, the Duke and #DuchessOfCambridge have shared a new portrait for his birthday, captured earlier this month in Norfolk by the Duchess. Click the link in bio for more on the touching image.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by British Vogue on July 21, 2021 tagging @jilsander, and @hereu_. May be an image of 1 person, indoor and text that says 'VOGUE'.

node.text:
Having been sworn to secrecy about her breakout role as Xialing in Marvel’s Asian-led #ShangChi and the Legend of the Ten Rings, Meng’er Zhang speaks to @SoeyKim about the significance of one of the year’s most anticipated blockbusters. “Shang-Chi will touch home, especially for Asian immigrants living in Western countries,” she says. “We need to remember our roots and be proud of where we’re from.” See the full story in the August 2021 issue of #BritishVogue, on newsstands now.

@Zhang_Meng_er photographed by @CharlotteHadden and styled by @RebeccaPurshouse.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by British Vogue on July 21, 2021 tagging @jodiemcomer. May be an image of 2 people and people standing.

node.text: For those left with a longing for medieval-style combat since #GameOfThrones ended, let #TheLastDuel fill the void. The film, directed by #RidleyScott, is a big-screen reimagining of Eric Jager’s nonfiction work about the last recorded trial by combat in 14th-century France, starring #JodieComer, #MattDamon, #AdamDriver and #BenAffleck – need we say more? Click the link in bio for a first look at the trailer.

node.text: It’s not a bag. It’s a Baguette. Die-hard #SexAndTheCity fans will know the significance of #CarrieBradshaw’s cult @Fendi accessory – the archetypal It bag was the first major designer piece to appear in the character’s now legendary wardrobe. And though early glimpses from the set of #AndJustLikeThat suggest the columnist’s look has evolved now she’s in her fifties, rest assured she’s refusing to be parted from this particular fashion classic. Click the link in bio for more on the Baguette’s cameo in the SATC reboot.

node.text: Last week was full of epic red-carpet moments at Cannes, but the crew-neck jumper #JasonSudeikis wore for the season two premiere of #TedLasso in LA put them all in the shade. Why? The simple slogan on the front: Jadon & Marcus & Bukayo. A gesture of support for the three gifted Black footballers subjected to racial abuse online in the wake of England’s heartbreaking Euro 2020 defeat at Wembley a week ago, Sudeikis had the top printed up himself before the event. At the link in bio, he discusses how the young players “led by example” during the tournament – and why more must be done to kick racism out of sport for good.
